body:
# Notion Blocks

Blocks are the building blocks of all Notion content. Every element inside a page — from a simple paragraph to a complex toggle with nested content — is a block. The Blocks API allows agents to retrieve, update, delete, and append blocks to pages.

## Block Types

Notion supports a wide range of block types:

| Block Type | API Type Key | Supports Children |
|-----------|-------------|-------------------|
| Paragraph | `paragraph` | Yes |
| Heading 1 | `heading_1` | Yes (toggleable) |
| Heading 2 | `heading_2` | Yes (toggleable) |
| Heading 3 | `heading_3` | Yes (toggleable) |
| Bulleted list | `bulleted_list_item` | Yes (sub-items) |
| Numbered list | `numbered_list_item` | Yes (sub-items) |
| To-do | `to_do` | Yes (sub-items) |
| Toggle | `toggle` | Yes (required) |
| Callout | `callout` | Yes |
| Quote | `quote` | Yes |
| Code | `code` | No |
| Divider | `divider` | No |
| Table | `table` | Yes (table_row) |
| Image | `image` | No |
| Bookmark | `bookmark` | No |
| Embed | `embed` | No |
| Equation | `equation` | No |
| Column list | `column_list` | Yes (column) |

## Nesting

Blocks that support children can contain other blocks, creating nested structures. Toggles are the most common parent block — their content is hidden until expanded. List items nest to create sub-lists. Headings can optionally be toggleable. Maximum nesting depth varies by block type.

```javascript
const { Client } = require('@notionhq/client');
const notion = new Client({ auth: process.env.NOTION_TOKEN });

// Toggle with nested content
await notion.blocks.children.append({
  block_id: pageId,
  children: [
    {
      type: 'toggle',
      toggle: {
        rich_text: [{ text: { content: 'Click to expand' } }],
        children: [
          {
            type: 'paragraph',
            paragraph: {
              rich_text: [{ text: { content: 'Hidden content revealed!' } }]
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
});
```

## Append Children

Append blocks to a page or parent block with `PATCH /v1/blocks/{block_id}/children` or `notion.blocks.children.append()`. Blocks are added at the end of the existing content. To insert at a specific position, use the `after` parameter with a block ID.

```javascript
// Append multiple block types
await notion.blocks.children.append({
  block_id: pageId,
  children: [
    {
      type: 'heading_2',
      heading_2: {
        rich_text: [{ text: { content: 'Section Title' } }]
      }
    },
    {
      type: 'paragraph',
      paragraph: {
        rich_text: [
          { text: { content: 'Regular text ' } },
          { text: { content: 'bold text' }, annotations: { bold: true } },
          { text: { content: ' and ' } },
          { text: { content: 'code' }, annotations: { code: true } }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      type: 'code',
      code: {
        rich_text: [{ text: { content: 'console.log("hello");' } }],
        language: 'javascript'
      }
    },
    {
      type: 'callout',
      callout: {
        icon: { type: 'emoji', emoji: '⚠️' },
        rich_text: [{ text: { content: 'Important note here.' } }]
      }
    }
  ]
});
```

## Rich Text

All text content in blocks uses the rich text object format. Each rich text element has:

- **text.content** — the plain text string
- **text.link** — optional URL link (null if none)
- **annotations** — formatting: `bold`, `italic`, `strikethrough`, `underline`, `code` (booleans), and `color` (string)
- **type** — `text`, `mention`, or `equation`

Mentions can reference pages (`{ page: { id } }`), databases (`{ database: { id } }`), users (`{ user: { id } }`), or dates (`{ date: { start, end } }`).

```javascript
// Rich text with multiple annotations
const richText = [
  { text: { content: 'Normal ' } },
  { text: { content: 'bold' }, annotations: { bold: true } },
  { text: { content: ', ' } },
  { text: { content: 'italic' }, annotations: { italic: true } },
  { text: { content: ', ' } },
  {
    text: { content: 'linked text', link: { url: 'https://notion.so' } },
    annotations: { underline: true, color: 'blue' }
  }
];
```
